## What's Next

Now that I have a better understanding of how Gopher and Gemini work, and have some tooling to make things seamless between gopher/gemini/web my plans are to improve `updatesmallweb.sh` so it's almost a static site generator. Some of the documentation and examples needs updating as well, so others can use it, and already gemini://gemini.lottalinuxlinks.com[13] has.

=> gemini://gemini.lottalinuxlinks.com 13: gemini://gemini.lottalinuxlinks.com

Gemini is one of those things that you either really like or don't quite understand it. I'm in the former group, as it reminds me of what the Internet was before it turned into what it is today. The phrase "Eternal August" is one that comes to mind, as it's specification is not meant to really be improved upon and should remain the same for the foreseeable future. This allows creativity to flourish in a restricted environment, like the Demo Scene or modern homebrew Gameboy Games.

For more on exploring Geminispace, see awesome-gemini[14].

=> https://github.com/kr1sp1n/awesome-gemini 14: https://github.com/kr1sp1n/awesome-gemini

